3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with optimization of pseudo-Boolean functions, which can be seen as a problem in information theory. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with analyzing the running time of algorithms on a specific class of functions, which can be seen as a problem in discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper provides lower bounds on the running time of evolutionary algorithms, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory.
